# Univariate histograms
# Histograms provide a bar chart of a numeric attribute splitinto bins with the height showing the number of instances thatfall into each bin. They are useful to get an indication of the distribution of an attribute.

# load the data
data(iris)
# create histograms for each attribute
par(mfrow=c(1,4))
for(i in 1:4) {
	hist(iris[,i], main=names(iris)[i])
}

Iris1 <- lm(Sepal.Length ~ Sepal.Width, data=iris)

Iris1
summary(Iris1)
#You can see that most of the attributes show a Gaussian or multi-modal Gaussian distribution. You can see the measurements of very small flowers in the Petal width and length column.